  <discussion>Plants of var. purshii were placed by G. B. Rossbach (1958) in three species
        (Erysimum angustatum, E. argillosum, E. desertorum) and by R. C. Rollins (1993) in two
        species (E. angustatum, E. capitatum). The considerable overlap in morphology and the
        frequent hybridization between vars. capitatum and purshii in areas where their geographical
        ranges meet argue against such delimitation. Forms with linear leaves to 3 mm wide, which
        are restricted to eastern Alaska and western Yukon, were recognized by Rossbach and Rollins
        as E. angustatum, but these hardly differ from typical var. purshii in all other
        characters.</discussion>
